```
wndc.lpfnWndProc = WNDPROC;
```

[`WNDPROC`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/desktop/legacy/ms633573(v%3Dvs.85)) is a type, not a variable. `lpfnWndProc` expects a pointer to a function that matches the signature defined by `WNDPROC`, eg:

```
#include &lt;windows.h&gt;

LRESULT CALLBACK MyWindowProc(HWND hwnd, UINT&#160;uMsg, WPARAM wParam, LPARAM lParam)
{
	switch (uMsg)
	{
		...
		case WM_DEVICECHANGE:
		{
			...
			break;
		}
		...
	}

	return DefWindowProc(hwnd, uMsg, wParam, lParam);
}

int CreateDetectWindow()
{
	...
	wndc.lpfnWndProc = &amp;MyWindowProc; 
	...
}
```

